-- TAKE A LOOK-U.S. navy black box locator joins Malaysian jet search 
-- 
-- Mon Mar 24, 2014 01:26AM EDT
-- None



March 24 (Reuters) -    The United States Navy is moving a high-tech black box detector closer to the search area for a Malaysia Airlines jet that vanished with 239 people aboard on March 8. The move strengthens hopes rescuers could soon find wreckage of the plane.

